            ===Etymology===
            {{root|en|ine-pro|*prehâ‚‚-}}
            From {{inh|en|enm|for}}, from {{inh|en|ang|for||for, because of}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*furi||for}}, from
            {{der|en|ine-pro|*prehâ‚‚-}}.
            Cognate with {{cog|fy|foar||for}}, {{cog|nl|voor||for}}, {{cog|de|fÃ¼r||for}}, {{cog|da|for||for}},
            {{cog|sv|fÃ¶r||for}}, {{cog|no|for||for}}, {{cog|is|fyrir||for}}, {{cog|la|per||by, through, for, by means
            of}} and Romance language successors (e.g. {{cog|es|para||for}}), {{cog|grc|Ï€ÎµÏÎ¯||for, about, toward}},
            {{cog|lt|per||by, through, during}}, {{cog|sa|à¤ªà¤°à¤¿||over, around|tr=pÃ¡ri}}.
