            =====Synonyms=====
            * {{sense|propel oneself upwards}} {{l|en|leap}}, {{l|en|spring}}
            * {{sense|cause oneself to leave an elevated location and fall}} {{l|en|jump down}}, {{l|en|jump off}}
            * {{sense|employ a parachute to leave an aircraft or elevated location}} {{l|en|skydive}}
            * {{sense|react to a sudden stimulus by jerking the body violently}} {{l|en|flinch}}, {{l|en|jerk}},
            {{l|en|jump out of one's skin}}, {{l|en|leap out of one's skin}}, {{l|en|twitch}}
            * {{sense|move to a position in a queue/line}} {{l|en|skip}}
            * {{sense|attack suddenly and violently}} {{l|en|ambush}}, {{l|en|assail}}; see also [[Thesaurus:attack]]
            * {{sense|engage in sexual intercourse}} {{l|en|hump}}, {{l|en|jump someone's bones}}; see also
            [[Thesaurus:copulate with]]
            * {{sense|bore with a jumper}} see also [[Thesaurus:make a hole]]
            * {{sense|make one's escape}} {{l|en|beat it}}, {{l|en|rabbit}}, {{l|en|take off}}; see also
            [[Thesaurus:flee]]
